# Chart Design Rules

## Container Rules (CRITICAL — prevents Recharts crashes)
- EVERY chart must be inside a div with `style={{ minHeight: NUMBER_IN_PIXELS }}`
- NEVER use `height="100%"` on ResponsiveContainer
- ALWAYS use `<ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={NUMBER}>` with a pixel value
- Minimum heights: stat cards 80px, small charts 160px, main charts 200px

## Recharts Styling
- NO gridlines (`<CartesianGrid>` removed or `strokeDasharray="0"` with opacity 0)
- NO Y axis (hide it: `<YAxis hide />`)
- X axis: show only date labels, no line, no ticks (`axisLine={false} tickLine={false}`)
- Stroke width: 1.5px for lines, 1px for area borders
- Fill opacity: 0.12 for area charts
- Bar border radius: 2px (`radius={[2, 2, 0, 0]}`)
- Tooltip: minimal, dark bg, white text, no border, small font
- Legend: never show — use inline labels or color coding

## Colors
- Lumière charts: stroke `#3d6b4a`, fill `#3d6b4a` at 0.12 opacity
- Ombre charts: stroke `#7a5163`, fill `#7a5163` at 0.12 opacity
- Neutre: `#5c5c5c`
- On dark backgrounds: increase opacity to 0.18 for visibility

## Stat Cards
- Number: `text-3xl font-medium` with `tabular-nums`
- Label: `text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider` in muted color
- Layout: flex row, gap-4, items-center or items-baseline
- No borders, no bg — just text on the panel bg
- Optionally: tiny sparkline next to the number (16px height)

## Responsive
- On screens < 768px: charts stack vertically, full width
- On screens >= 768px: charts can be side by side (grid-cols-2)
- Always maintain minHeight even on mobile
